html.body: APC module CDC20 and CDH1 are proteins of the APC (Anaphase Promoting Complex) that tags proteins for ubiquitination. CDC20 binds to the APC and cyclins to the APC for degradation during M phase (PMID:15577895). CDC20 activity is shut off in early G1 whereas CDH1 remains active throughout G1 phase and is inactivated at the G1/S transition. CDH1 binds to APC in its unphosphorylated form and mediates the degradation of CycA2/CDK2 (PMID:15840442).
